/**
  ******************************************************************************
  * @file           : main.c
  * @brief          : Main program body
  ******************************************************************************
  * HC-SR04 ultrasonic sensor using TIM5 input capture interrupt
  *
  * pin choice:
  *   TRIG -> PA5  (GPIO output)
  *   ECHO -> PA0  (TIM5_CH1)
  *
  * How it works:
  *   1. The STM32 sends a short 10 us pulse to TRIG.
  *   2. The HC-SR04 sends ultrasonic waves.
  *   3. The ECHO pin goes HIGH until the reflected wave comes back.
  *   4. TIM5 input capture interrupt records the rising edge and falling edge.
  *   5. The difference between those two timer values gives the pulse width.
  *   6. The pulse width is converted into distance in centimeters.
  *
  ******************************************************************************
  */
